                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.24/12–1444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-14T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 14, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2017. From Wiley.<note n="58" xml:id="d784fn58">John C. Wiley, Ambassador
                        Designate to Colombia.</note> Thank you for your 1373, December 13, 4
                        p.m.<note n="59" xml:id="d784fn59">Not printed; the Department instructed
                        that conversations be suspended on the Colombian request for rifles
                        (821.24/12–1344).</note> I had not intended to discuss matter until raised
                    by Colombian Government. I regret that attitude of OPD<note n="60"
                        xml:id="d784fn60">Operations Division.</note> of the War Department has
                    apparently made it necessary for the Colombian Government to turn to the Mexican
                    Government for equipment for the National Police. [Wiley.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
